  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for glib2",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for glib2 fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2026-1485: Fixed buffer underflow and out-of-bounds access due to integer wraparound in content type parsing (bsc#1257354).\n- CVE-2026-1484: Fixed buffer underflow and out-of-bounds access due to miscalculated buffer boundaries in the Base64 encoding routine (bsc#1257355).\n- CVE-2026-1489: Fixed undersized heap allocation followed by out-of-bounds access due to integer overflow in Unicode case conversion (bsc#1257353).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
